  "body": "\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nWe ran the deploy test network and the blocks were synchronizing, but when I called  eth_syncing rpc interface returns a result of false. This means that this block has been synchronized with the latest, when I go to call ETH_ When blockNumber is reached, the height of the block continues to grow. eth_ The data returned by syncing is incorrect, which leads to a logical error in the external health check probe.\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n/ # curl localhost:8545 -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_syncing\",\"params\":[],\"id\":1}'\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":false}\r\n/ # curl localhost:8545 -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_blockNumber\",\"params\":[],\"id\":1}'\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":\"0x7ba2e3\"}\r\n/ # curl localhost:8545 -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_blockNumber\",\"params\":[],\"id\":1}'\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":\"0x7ba31a\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nWhen the block height is not synchronized with the latest, call the  `eth_syncing` following result should be returned\r\n\r\n\r\nresult - The result is false if JSON Object is not syncing otherwise it's true:\r\n- startingblock - The block at which the import started encoded as hexadecimal\r\n\r\n- currentblock - The current block, same as eth_blockNumber encoded as hexadecimal\r\n\r\n- highestblock - The estimated highest block encoded as hexadecimal\r\n\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nAdd any other context about the problem here.\r\nop-geth:  us-docker.pkg.dev/oplabs-tools-artifacts/images/op-geth:latest\r\nop-node:  us-docker.pkg.dev/oplabs-tools-artifacts/images/op-node:latest\r\n",
