    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The `eth_syncing` result corresponds to the geth long-range syncing, which Optimism currently does not utilize, since everything is processed block-by-block from L1 data. However, because the block-time is fixed, you can see if it's synced up by comparing the timestamp of the latest block with the expected timestamp on your system clock, with a margin of a few seconds.\r\n\r\nAlso try `optimism_syncStatus` on the op-node for detailed sync progress information.\r\n\r\nAnd `net_peerCount` is expected to be 0 on op-geth. It syncs via p2p in the op-node instead, see p2p API here: https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/develop/op-node/p2p/rpc_api.go (we're still working on docs for advanced functionality), specifically try `opp2p_peers true` on op-node to get a list of connected peers.",
